<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $a ∈ 𝗥$ and $f: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ defined by $f(x) = a^x$. ⦉

  ‖ Then $f$ is differentiable and its derivative is the
    function $f': 𝗥 → 𝗥$ defined by $f'(x) = \ln(a)a^x$. ⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ This proposition encompasses the special case $f(x) = e^x$
    then $f'(x) = e^x$. ⦉
⦉

